*OWASP Top 10*

OWASP Top 10 is a list of the most critical web application security risks. It helps developers understand common vulnerabilities and build secure applications.

OWASP Top 10 Vulnerabilities
Broken Access Control
Users can access unauthorized data or functions.

Cryptographic Failures
Weak encryption or improper handling of sensitive data.

Injection
Malicious code or queries are inserted into the application (e.g., SQL Injection).

Insecure Design
Security flaws due to poor application design.

Security Misconfiguration
Improper security settings, default passwords, or unnecessary features enabled.

Vulnerable and Outdated Components
Using old libraries or frameworks with known vulnerabilities.

Identification and Authentication Failures
Weak login systems, poor password handling, or broken authentication.

Software and Data Integrity Failures
Untrusted software updates or insecure CI/CD pipelines.

Security Logging and Monitoring Failures
Lack of proper logging and monitoring for detecting attacks.

Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF)
Attackers force the server to make unauthorized requests to internal/external systems.

*Importance of OWASP Top 10*

Helps developers build secure applications
Identifies common attack methods
Improves application security awareness
Acts as a guideline for secure coding practices